td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Soloing spot 34 thru 39</span><hr size=1> Found a new soloing spot that I have never seen mentioned up here for levels 34 thru 39.<br>
<br>
Firiona Vie...  South East corner of map.. close to the edge of the map, close to the cliff.<br>
<br>
You can pull single Drolvargs who wander about in that part of the woods.  Old fashioned snare, root, and shoot works just fine and you don't need sow.  Medding near the edge of the cliff is pretty safe as the Drolvargs tend not to wander close to the edge, but make sure to med at the edge that is furthest from the forest.  Very solitary place.  Didn't even see a single player character walk by.<br>
<br>
Things to watch out for are the pilgrims and the butterflies.  No they won't hurt you, they are actually amiable to me... but they will kill steal from you.  I would suggest against AE kiting these Drolvargs because if a pilgrim or a butterfly agro's on the Drolvargs, your AE will hit them as well and killing them will ruin FV faction.  But if you get in trouble, run to a pilgrim or butterfly... they will help you out.  Overall it's a very safe place to solo... Not recommended for Dark Elf Wizards though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uorsmoxlorr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orsmo Xlorr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/01 8:24:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> thanks</span><hr size=1> Now that you mention this spot I do remember a few levels ago trying to head back up to FoB and getting lost in this zone.  Over where you are talking about i ran into one other player and that is exactly the tactics they were using.  If memory serves it was a wizard but I don't remember her name.  But i do concur with the fact that this area is seldom used and not heavy on the Mob gatherings.<br>
<br>
Orsmo Xlorr<br>
38 lvl wizard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udzieger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DZieger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/01 10:28:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing spot 34 thru 39</span><hr size=1> Sounds good - I may try this tonight.<br>
<br>
Certainly beats hopping the boat to the golras in TD.<br>
(hope it works at 33 too)<br>
<br>
Zardain Tachyon<br>
33 Wiz of Zeb<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulsyw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lsyw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/01 4:36:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing spot 34 thru 39</span><hr size=1> How far South East are we talking here? I'm not familiar with the area. Just out the ramp and follow the cliff to the end? Thanks <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukaedir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaedir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/01 8:29:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing spot 34 thru 39</span><hr size=1> &quot;... Not recommended for Dark Elf Wizards though.&quot;<br>
<br>
doh, u got me all excited about a new soloing spot until i saw that, o well, back kiting gnolls for me.<br>
<br>
-Kaedir <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspankda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spankda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 5:39:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Dark Elf Wizard Kiting</span><hr size=1> If you're a dark elf wizard,  you should be at The Overthere where you're *not* KoS to the Dragoons.<br>
<br>
The Overthere is an awesome zone.  Long, flat stretches of land to kite, blue, yellow, and red mobs for a 34.  A safety net at the Outpost when things go bad.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.vanderwerken.com/spankda.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <br>
<br>
Spankda <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=berdug0>berdug0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 2:16:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing spot 34 thru 39</span><hr size=1> Yes, just follow the cliff until you reach the very end of it.  It's at the very SW corner of the cliff.<br>
<br>
Drolvargs work on Pack of Tomor faction.  Only reason I don't recommend it for Dark Elves is because FV is a High Elf city and DE's are KOS, unless you've upped your faction hunting in LOIO in your 20's.<br>
<br>
Reason why not alot of people hunt here, despite the fact these Drolvargs give just as good exp as OverThere and better loot... is the Drolvargs hit like a machine gun.  They touch you, you're a goner.<br>
<br>
Luckily they are snare and root- able... perfect wiz food.  And don't forget you're safety net.  The FV guards, pilgrims, and butterflies will kill the drolvargs if you get into trouble.  Kinda feels like a newbie zone because of that.  Very safe indeed.<br>
<br>
Good luck! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uixiathewhite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IxiatheWhite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 10:24:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Keep an eye out for those drixies</span><hr size=1> First of all, this is a good solo place for xp. Loot blows.<br>
<br>
However, let me *bump* the earlier caution - take care throwing BoF around. I was going along hunting just fine, wandered back to the bridge, and got the message that BoF had worn off. Huh? I killed the Drolvarg, didn't I?<br>
<br>
Two minutes later two pilgrims had teamed up with the drixie I had (apparently) BoF'd by accident, caught up with me, and slaughtered me in the middle of medding, right in front of the guards.<br>
<br>
Traumatized the poor dwarf next to me...dunno if he'll ever recover...<br>
<br>
Anyway, keep your eyes peeled. BoF works great on blue drolvargs, but be kind to the locals. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulsyw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lsyw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/8/01 10:49:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Keep an eye out for those drixies</span><hr size=1> My 2 cps <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
You need SoW. These doggies run fast.<br>
<br>
Resists aren't too bad, overall; growlers/Scavengers appear to have the less resists while Snarlers seem to resist more.<br>
<br>
I ususally start with either snare or root. If resist on snare, run out, root, snare, shoot.<br>
<br>
If pilgrims or drixies aggro while you're engaged, try and nuke the thing dead before they do the job <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
I med at the cliff across from a tree and close to the Tracker NPC that hangs out in that area. Just run along until you see a solitary tree, sit across from it close to the cliff edge (you know you're close to the edge when you hear the gulls <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    ) I've had the doggies pass me by without aggro while sitting here<br>
<br>
Had the doggies catch up and hit me a few times. Usually in these circumstances, root and run or just run. Have Steelskin up, I've had 4-5 hits and the skin was still up <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Loot isn't too bad <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
One last thing, not sure if it's a bug or not but if you run too far away after snare, the doggies will lost interest. Also, I've had the doggies pop right on top of me after I ran too far away from them (but only after I had nuked it has this happened)  <br>
<br>
My 2 cps and good luck <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulsyw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lsyw</A> at: 7/8/01 10:55:59 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umdarkelf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mdar kelf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/12/01 1:24:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Keep an eye out for those drixies</span><hr size=1> not a bug<br>
things in kunark and vel will loose interest if they loose sight of you, but will stay agroed on you as long as you are in the zone, as my bard i have had faction changes during down time cause of it, hehe, they cant keep up with that drum<br>
also things do seem to be able to find you at odd times...<br>
oh well, good luck <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ffffff>- </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation>Graffë's Wizard Discussion</a><font color=#ffffff> - </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19>Soloing</a> <font color=#ffffff> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.3.7<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  